<subsection xml:id="subsec-express-numbers-in-index-form">
    <title>Expressing Numbers in Index Form</title>
    <p>
        When we have:
    </p>
    <p>
        <me>
            2^3 = 2 \times 2 \times 2
        </me>
    </p>
    <p>
        <me>
            = 8
        </me>
    </p>
    <p>
        2 is the base, 3 is the index, and we get <m>8</m> as the answer.
    </p>
    <p>
        Therefore we can say, if <m>x</m> is a whole number;
    </p>
    <p>
        <me>
            x^a = x \times x \times x .......(a is the number of times)
        </me>
    </p>
    <p>
        Example:
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>a^2</m> = <m>a \times a</m>  (<m>a</m> - two times)
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>2^3</m> = <m>2 \times 2 \times 2</m>  (<m>2</m> - three times)
    </p>
    <p>
        <m> = 8</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>5^4</m> = <m>5 \times 5 \times 5 \times 5</m>  (<m>5</m> - four times)
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>= 625</m>
    </p>
</subsection>